Power was sucked out of my sisters and mother in one form another. #domesticviolence #sexualabuse #shame and #sadness ... these are the words that defined the ones nearest and dearest to me... including myself. There once was a fire in me, one that could light up a room and set it into flames from my passion alone. I keep trying to pinpoint a moment in time when that started to dim, and I realize it was gradual. It started with â€œyou talk too muchâ€, â€œnice girls...do Xâ€, or that my looks were my greatest ASSet (implicitly on too many levels to count)... so, I shrank, I got smaller and things like normal, natural teenage acne crushed my self-perception. Was it vanity? No. A sick society, one that teaches women that building their ass is more important than building a strong mind. I was merely a product.Now, I attend therapy like itâ€™s my fucking religion, while I lick my wounds from the pain of the time I lost being in my power. But I am waking up.We shrug and sigh when yet again another woman is raped, another girl is abused, another mother is beaten to a pulp, when in fact we should be fighting.Not fighting in the literal sense, but rather calling on the rage from the depths of our soul that was pushed down, â€œmakeup uppedâ€, swallowed, subdued, ignored, downplayed... that was asked to play nice and sit pretty like a good little girl.Fuck nice and fuck pretty.. it is boring, sad and leads to an unlived life.What is your greatest asset?#womenempowerment #femaleempowerment #revolution #feminism #anger #eatingdisorder #womenshealth

I promise you this.Don't fall prey to the voice of your mind convincing you of all the reasons why you're just not good enough.Remember that last very special time when nobody thought you'd survive, AND YOU DID?.Dig deep for even an ounce of strength left within you. Growing up means learning what life is. When you're little, you have a set of ideals, standards, criteria, plans, outlooks, and you think that you have to sit around and wait for them to happen to you and then life will work. But life isn't like that, for anybody; you can't fall in love with a standard, you have to fall in love with a person. You can't live in a criteria, you have to live your life. You can't wait for your plans to materialize, because they may never materialize the way you think they will. You can't wait to watch your ideals and standards walk up to you, because you can't know what's yours until you have it. I always say, always take the first chance in case you never get a second one, but growing up takes that even one step further, growing up means that you have to hold on to what you have, when you have it, because what you have- that's yours- and all the ideals and criteria you have set in your head, those aren't yours, because those haven't happened to you.-C. (Luke 22: 31-32)No matter how long we've been walking with God, we should always be mindful that spiritual warfare is never to be underestimated. In verse 31 Jesus calls Peter "Simon", even though it was Him who changed Peter's name in the 1st place, (John 1:42). But Peter was His spiritual name, Simon was his natural name and at the time Jesus was speaking to the natural side of Peter and the message He had for Peter was so serious that He called him by his natural name twice.Jesus wanted Peter to know that Satan desired to put him through a test, a serious test, one that Peter would later fail, but the Lord wasn't concerned with Peter passing the test (if He was He would have prayed for him to have victory), He was more concerned with what mattered the most, his faith. People often ask why didn't God just stop Peter from being tested in the 1st place? But how often does God stop any of us from bring tested? If God never allowed us to be tested, we would all be a weak bunch of Christians, unable to withstand the intensity of spiritual warfare. We may see Peter as a failure because he failed his test. But to God, Peter was a winner because his faith stayed in tact. It's our faith in God that makes us a winner and when we make the choice to keep our faith in spite of spiritual warfare, we grow stronger and prove to God that we are fit for service and able to handle His blessings!Don't quit because you failed or because you don't understand - that's exactly what the enemy wants you to do. He's the one who's telling you to quit. Even though you failed, even though you don't understand, you keep your faith! Don't ever lose your faith! Who can relate? â . â For many reasons, navigating the roller coaster of life (largely including being a mom), I can be left DRAINED at the end of the day. â . â Last night was one such day. It was compounded by my husband coming home from work in the same space- exhausted. â . â I've talked about increasing your awareness around what you need, and honestly, last night, I don't think either one of us knew what we needed or how to support each other.â .â I could feel the energy between us being on the verge of an argument, purely because we didn't have any capacity left. â . â It wasn't until we were brushing our teeth together, did I realize what we needed. That single moment made the entire day manageable by being able to release the tension built up in my body and laugh with my loved one. â . â I hope this helps you. Last evening we went, me and the lake fairy, to have a picnic supper by a lake. There were creatures. I enjoy taking pics of creatures on things. Here are some: a Carder Bee, Bombus Pascuorum on a thistle. Marmelade hover fly on air. Some kind of Calligrapher hover fly on chicory. A Napoleon spider on an ox eye daisy. A Burnet Companion moth also on Weedknap. A very hairy caterpillar, possibly a fox moth, on a small oak sapling. A False oil beetle on ox eye. Furrow beetle wrapping up a fly on its web A beautiful damsel fly not in any kind of distress and finally beat us vitale eligans balancing delicately on a dandelion. #creatures #lake #fairy #picnic #insects #beetles #spiders #hoverfly #wildflowers #joyful #nature #naturephotography

I wouldn't normally expose my personal business on social media like this. I want to think my family & friends for all the support encouraging words,  faith , hope the strength & praying .  all the phone calls etc.. Without yall and God I  wouldn't have got threw this message from god alone!! But I want the world to see my miracle baby.What Gods Angel's looks like.My baby had a seizure for 1hr straight they gave her every Medication for seizures for adults and children.. my baby stopped breathing ..The machine was breathing for her.She was flown to the main Childrens Hospital campus and woke up twice trying to take the tubes and cords off her.. But they had to put her back to sleep cause if the breathing tubes came out she would not Make it. The Drs excepted her to wake up on her own at some point days later.They couldn't wake her  up ... they said she had to do it on her own.. my baby woke up at 1am that night.. they put her back to sleep.. cause she tried taken  the breathing tubes out again. And this time she tried getting out the hospital bed.I was so distraught and didnt know what to think. I felt like I was cut with a razor and my heart was snatched out my chest. I though i had to bury my baby. I dont ever wish this feeling on no one.. my baby kissed me before she seized out .. I felt she told me good bye!!!Love on your kids and family cause you never know when there time will expire!!! #godchild #godschildren  ##beautiful #blessed #greatful #faith #family #prayingwarrior #prayingfamily #loveyourkids #unconditionallove #life

Last night was a bit chaotic. Around 2am I noticed our stringer lights outside had turned off on their own. As I looked out of our bedroom window, a constant flicker of heat lightening revealed the forest floor was moving. I thought I was hallucinating, or having another flood nightmare.. so I grabbed a flashlight and opened our front door. The water was already up to our second step and almost to the top of the camper tires.After some intense scrambling we waded through the thigh high water and to our vehicles, which were right in the middle of where the driveway was being washed out. We drove up to higher ground and waited. About half an hour later the water had already receded most of the way and I took this short video.A lot of folks in Carlisle lost their homes last night. We're extremely lucky our camper didn't get washed away or flooded.
